caption:
Letting imaginations run wild one @Kozycouch at a time. #ad Castles and bridges aren‚Äôt just for story books anymore. My kids love being able to bring their imaginations to life and I love the energy they burn while doing it! They are a #momwin and definitely #kidapproved 

I especially love that when the play is set to rest for the day we can fold them up and they work perfect as an ottoman or extra seat right in our living room! 

P.S. They are just a couple inches shy of a twin bed and make great sleepover or indoor camp out pallets!
#ad Aspen is all smiles for her @kozycouch ü§ç

I don‚Äôt even know üòÇ
*
*
*
I‚Äôve been in a funk/ break from Instagram y‚Äôall! After months and months of cranking out the content I feel like I‚Äôm finally hitting that invisible wall lol! But reels are where it‚Äôs at so I hope you guys enjoy the twins being their naturally silly selves ü•∞

This little break is 100% temporary of course but just wanted to share where I‚Äôm at. I really do appreciate all the check up messages! And the twins are doing just fine too! I promise to try my hardest to still show up so you guys can see the twins ü•∞

Thank you always for the love and support! The Instafam love is definitely the best part of Instagram ‚ù§Ô∏è

Anyone else in a creative drought or Instagram break mood? 
*
*
*

Sharing one of our must have items, the @kozycouch play couch set. #sponsored

Sleeping on your back in pregnancy.  What have you heard? 

Your body will likely shift to the side if you fall asleep on your back later in pregnancy.  And don‚Äôt freak out if you have slept on your back. 

When you lie on your back, it compresses the blood vessels and can lead to shortness of breath, dizziness, and a possible decrease in blood flow to baby.  That is why sleeping on your side is usually suggested. 

Check out ACOG for more! And be sure to ask your doc for tips! 

And if you are looking for an amazing pillow to try for side sleeping, you need to check out these awesome pillows that I was sent from @necklowco !  I‚Äôll never share a product I didn‚Äôt review, and I promise this one does what it says it will do! Highly recommend!

#ad Slow starts to the morning around here today. How cute is this mug and throw from @ecletticos ? How do you start your day?

Home goods aren't all about making your house look good‚Äîthey're about crafting a space to feel like home. They're an expression of our true selves, and that's why they bring us comfort.

mug is more than just a cup to hold your brew‚Äîit's a morning companion that meets you up bright and early everyday.

utmost eclectic collection of goods to transform routine events into something meaningful‚Äîby having creative

#coffee #slowmorning #coffeemug #butfirstcoffee #greyaesthetic #throwblanket #momentsintime #momentsofmine #morningroutine

I have never been so excited to receive something ü•∞ My new coffee/tea mug from @ecletticos is not just SO pretty but also is so useful. It has a tea strainer so you can hame your tea or you can remove the strainer and have coffee or whatever! I am loving this mug and the most exciting part is the name of the mug is NEPAL tea/coffee mug Ahhhhh that just made my day. The Nepal Coffee & Tea Mug is a complete work of art with meticulously crafted landscape designs and natural colors that blend together to deliver an amazing ceramic cup with the wooden handle. üôåüèΩüôèüèΩ

caption:
Being in my 20s I know I have more freedom and less responsibility then I will have later in life. 
But no matter what I will always keep my youthful energy. I wanna be that 80 year old woman dancing barefoot in the park with her husband. Or that 40 year old laughing so hard she‚Äôs cries at the wine bar with her friends. Or that 30 year old hosting game nights and corn hole competitions. I want to live and feel everything always. So yeah I guess I do want to be forever young.
